# badurls/exclude_list
# --------------------
# One domain or identifying substring per line. Matching URLs are excluded from
# badurls extraction/aggregation. Blank lines and lines beginning with # are
# ignored by the 2026 Python utility.
#
# Add domains that are commonly cited in legitimate discussion or abuse reports
# and must never be promoted automatically into bad_url rules.
#
# Safe examples (disabled):
# wikipedia.org
# ietf.org
# github.com
# your-own-domain.example
#
# Prefer exact registrable domains. Avoid generic fragments such as "news",
# "mail", ".com", or "cdn".
